[assistant-event] text_start
[assistant] Fixed the failing test setup and amended the existing commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `ReflectionFactory.newConstructorForSerialization(...)` triggered initialization of `ObjectFactory`.
[assistant] - `ObjectFactory` has a static `Kernel32.INSTANCE`-dependent field, which fails on Linux with `Unable to load library 'kernel32'`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Replaced the `ReflectionFactory` allocation path with `Unsafe.allocateInstance(Factory.class)`.
[assistant] - This avoids constructor execution and avoids initializing the Windows-only `ObjectFactory` static state before exercising `Factory.createProxy(...)`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated commit:
[assistant] - `2ffe18d07c Add JNA Factory proxy coverage test`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Working tree is clean. I did not run tests.
[assistant-event] text_end
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the failing test setup and amended the existing commit.\n\nCause:\n- `ReflectionFactory.newConstructorForSerialization(...)` triggered initialization of `ObjectFactory`.\n- `ObjectFactory` has a static `Kernel32.INSTANCE`-dependent field, which fails on Linux with `Unable to load library 'kernel32'`.\n\nFix:\n- Replaced the `ReflectionFactory` allocation path with `Unsafe.allocateInstance(Factory.class)`.\n- This avoids constructor execution and avoids initializing the Windows-only `ObjectFactory` static state before exercising `Factory.createProxy(...)`.\n\nUpdated commit:\n- `2ffe18d07c Add JNA Factory proxy coverage test`\n\nWorking tree is clean. I did not run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03e32479f4cf55c10169f2df79027c81a2829c152d0535a257\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 252, "output": 143, "cacheRead": 44544, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44939, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777524599642, "responseId": "resp_03e32479f4cf55c10169f2df78384481a2b52d2037144d93b7"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the failing test setup and amended the existing commit.\n\nCause:\n- `ReflectionFactory.newConstructorForSerialization(...)` triggered initialization of `ObjectFactory`.\n- `ObjectFactory` has a static `Kernel32.INSTANCE`-dependent field, which fails on Linux with `Unable to load library 'kernel32'`.\n\nFix:\n- Replaced the `ReflectionFactory` allocation path with `Unsafe.allocateInstance(Factory.class)`.\n- This avoids constructor execution and avoids initializing the Windows-only `ObjectFactory` static state before exercising `Factory.createProxy(...)`.\n\nUpdated commit:\n- `2ffe18d07c Add JNA Factory proxy coverage test`\n\nWorking tree is clean. I did not run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03e32479f4cf55c10169f2df79027c81a2829c152d0535a257\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 252, "output": 143, "cacheRead": 44544, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44939, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777524599642, "responseId": "resp_03e32479f4cf55c10169f2df78384481a2b52d2037144d93b7"}, "toolResults": []}
