[assistant] Fixed the fake `kernel32` callback calling convention and amended the commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - The fake `NativeLibrary` must be cached under the Windows `StdCallLibrary.STDCALL_CONVENTION` key because that is how JNA looks up `Kernel32` functions.
[assistant] - But the actual callback is executed on Linux, where invoking a JNA `Function` with calling convention `63` fails with `Unrecognized calling convention: 63`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Keep the cache key using `StdCallLibrary.STDCALL_CONVENTION`.
[assistant] - Create the callback-backed `Function` with `Function.C_CONVENTION`, so it can be invoked on Linux.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated commit:
[assistant] - `9ef9a3b340 Add JNA Factory proxy coverage test`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Working tree is clean. I did not run tests.
[assistant-event] text_end
